The paper discusses the application of machine learning techniques to two communications problems, indicating that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf learning packages, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper mentions the use of deep learning, indicating that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper discusses the system architecture and the gains observed, indicating that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of simulations, indicating that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
